Adaptations.description:
"The Guangxi Nanning Urban Environmental Upgrading Project is a key urban environmental improvement initiative of the Nanning municipal government (NMG) which aims to enhance the urban environment and public health in Nanning City. The incidence of waterborne and vector-borne diseases is expected to be reduced by 10% from the 2004 level. The Project comprises four subprojects:
(i) Xinxujiang River environmental upgrading, which will reduce flood risk, improve wastewater management, and
expand the green environment in the area along Xinxujiang River;
(ii) Kelijiang River environmental upgrading, which will reduce flood risk, improve wastewater management, and expand the green environment in the area along Kelijiang River within Xiangsihu New District;
(iii) solid waste management, which will strengthen the domestic solid waste management capacity and improve cleanliness of the streets;
(iv) Qingxiushan Park ecological upgrading, which will improve the environmental conditions and facilities of the park, a major tourism and recreational amenity in Nanning City, and thereby contribute to improvement of the city’s air quality, promote tourism, and increase people’s awareness of environmental protection. The Project will provide institutional capacity building and training on project management, operation and maintenance (O&M) of project facilities, and sustainable financial management of the implementing agencies (IAs)."

Adaptations.limiting_factors:
"The awareness of stakeholders is quite low;
The adaptation measures are quite expensive to take;
The co-ordination in water resources management is not really good to implementing the results proposed by project."

Adaptations.description:
"This project ultimately aims at mitigation of the impacts of the sea level rise due to climate change in Vietnam through propose adaptation measures. Its objectives are:
- To increase the knowledge on the methods of dealing with natural hazards due to climate change and the problem of sea level rise in Vietnam;
- To protect local communities, many of them belong to the poorest and most vulnerable to natural hazards as well as economic sectors in the coastal areas from adverse impacts of the sea level rise;
- To propose to the Vietnam government the strategies towards reasonable utilization of the resources of the coastal zone for economic and social development while protect the natural and social environment of the area."

Adaptations.outcome_evaluation:
"The project studies the impacts of sea water level rise on many field include:
- Potential impacts of saline water in spatial scale in the Red and Mekong River deltas and pilot study area;
- The vulnerability of ecological system and marine protected area;
- The cost – benefit analysis of adaptation measures in the pilot study area;
- Risk analysis and management.
The project is running and it will propose:
- Potential measures to mitigate the negative impacts on ecological system and marine protected area;
- Approaches to manage the risks of sea water level rise."

"The project is running and its expected outcomes objectives are:
- To compile flood hazard maps and climate function maps, grounding on GIS-based indicator mapping;
- To compile demand-oriented planning recommendation maps;
- To develop strategies and measures for climate change adaptation in Ho Chi Minh City
- To implement a planning study as a showcase for the adaptation of urban neighbourhoods;
- To develop and implement a Community Based Adaptation (CBA) Scheme to adapt low-income communities to climate change;
- To elaborate recommendations for institutional innovation in the Ho Chi Minh City Metropolitan Region to improve adaptive capacity;
- To support efforts regarding climate change adaptation and to integrate effective adaptation measures into urban planning in Ho Chi Minh City;
- To advance and disseminate climate change related knowledge, to inform decision makers and the general public about climate change risks;
- To increase capacity to implement necessary adaptation measures and to strengthen the resilience of the Ho Chi Minh City urban system."

Adaptations.success_factors:
"- Cooperation between Red Cross and scientists, relevant institutions and organizations;
- The project had the cooperation with many other organizations in 5 pilot provinces;
- The climate change messages were communicated to local people in simple ways."

Adaptations.outcome_evaluation:
"The project is running and result archived so far are:
- Capacity development for counterpart staff and staff of collaborating local authorities has created the preconditions necessary for the acceptance and implementation of new and innovative concepts;
- The People’s Committee of Soc Trang Province is supporting the project with the implementation of the new concept of co-management and innovative approaches to mangrove rehabilitation, as well as the establishment of inter-sectoral steering committees for integrated coastal zone management at province, district and communal levels;
- All relevant stakeholders support the implementation of co-management in the pilot site of Au Tho B village. Although the pilot study has not been completed yet, local authorities, in collaboration with the district authorities, have started to extend the concept to the communal level"
